<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: Opionion from a socio-pathic Pking 15-year old</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Koss">Koss</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 11:16 a.m. 10/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: Opionion from a socio-pathic Pking 15-year old<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=458" TARGET=_self>Opionion from a socio-pathic Pking 15-year old</A> (ZKHades)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>ZKHades -

<P>Sorry you took offense, but It was not intended. I was by no means implying that every rapid pker was a 15 year old. I was using the terms RealmWeaver stated in his editorial as to avoid confusion. More than you think pkers are not sociopathic teenagers, on the contrary there are just as many pkers over the age of 21 than there are below it.
<P>As for Lineage, I am sorry to say I never played that game much. I only signed on breifly during early alpha stages. On top of 75% of the people speaking a foreign language, I only found one room. Just one open plain with a town in the middle. If this was still the same when you were there, I can understand why a guard system worked so well. Its just a quick 60 second run to town no matter where you are : ) Would hardly be the case in everquest. In some spots there is a good half-hour run to the nearest friendly town.
<P>But that is not the point, guards could work in EQ just as they do in most games. It just would not be as effective and would not eliminate the problem of disgrunted and frustrated gamers who do not wish to partake in player vs player combat. I agree with you when you say that the current EQ system is the most effective, it is.
<P>Koss
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
